# racy_mutate -- a variant of mutate that may be shared between threads
#
# NYI: UNDER DEVELOPMENT: Currently, this does not do anything to make sure
# racy accesses are ok, i.e., there are no memory fences, there are no
# atomic operations and `exclusive` does not enforce exlusivity.  This is
# only an intermediate solution to permit sharing a mutate even though the
# resulting code is full of races.
#
# The idea is to remove this as soon as we have proper, thread-save effects
# using mutexes, memory fences, atomic operations, transations or other
# means to ensure thread-safety.
#
public racy_mutate : mutate is

  # test if the current thread is the same as the thread this mutate was created in
  #
  module redef correct_thread
  =>
    true
